This is another critical finding. The Exercises collection access control checks `owner` field (line 26 in Exercises/index.ts), but the field is actually named `createdBy`, not `owner`. Wait, looking more carefully at line 17-29 of Exercises/index.ts:

```typescript
const isAdminOrOwner: Access = ({ req }) => {
  const user = req.user as User | null
  if (!user) return false
  if (user.role === AccountRole.Admin) return true
  return {
    owner: { equals: user.id },
  }
}
```

This queries `owner` field in the collection. But the collection uses `createdByField` which defines the field name as `createdBy`. So this is an existing bug in the codebase, not introduced by this change. The endpoint, however, also checks `exercise.owner` (line 100), which will always be `undefined` since the field is `createdBy`.

